{"lemma":"أَخْصَبانِ","slug":"أَخْصَبانِ","root":"خ.ص.ب","root_slug":"خ-ص-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ص-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n10752","","n10758"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AE%D9%92%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of خَصِيب (ḵaṣīb):; more fertile; most fertile"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of خَصِيب (ḵaṣīb):; more prolific; most prolific"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Elative of خَصِيب (ḵaṣīb, “fertile; prolific”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10752","headword_ar":"اخصب","root":"xSb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ixoSaAbN","text_ar":"اـِخْصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) [and some add"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiSobN","text_ar":"خِصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as another inf. n.; but ISd holds this to be a simple subst.; (see 4 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ryf","text_ar":"ريف"},{"kind":"text","text":";)] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaSiba","text_ar":"خَصِبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaSaba","text_ar":"خَصَبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiSobN","text_ar":"خِصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a place)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became abundant, with herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the produce of the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the goods, conveniences,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comforts, of life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, fruitful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had increase; had plenty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajodaba","text_ar":"اَجْدَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadiba","text_ar":"جَدِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadaba","text_ar":"جَدَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaduba","text_ar":"جَدُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"page_break","n":748},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxSbt AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"اخصبت الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, abounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became abundant, with herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (JK, S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ixoSaAbN","text_ar":"اـِخْصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AixotiSaAbN","text_ar":"اِخْتِصَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are both from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxiSobu","text_ar":"الخِصْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but the precise meaning of the latter is not explained]. (Lth, JK, TA.) In the saying of the rájiz,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"laqado xa$iytu A^ano A^araY jadib~aA\n                      \n                     \n                        fiY EaAminaA *aA baEoda A^ano A^axoSab~aA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily I feared to see drought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barrenness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dearth, in this our year, after it had been abundant in herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoSab~aA","text_ar":"اَخْصَبَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoSabaA","text_ar":"اَخْصَبَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": but accord. to one reading, it is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AixoSab~aA","text_ar":"اِخْصَبَّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifoEal~a","text_ar":"اِفْعَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", though this is generally employed for colours; and the incipient"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is rendered disjunctive of necessity, for the sake of the metre. (L. [Respecting"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jidab~aA","text_ar":"جِدَبَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadobN","text_ar":"جَدْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxSb janaAbu Alqawomi","text_ar":"اخصب جَنَابُ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tract surrounding the people"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became abundant with herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxSbwA","text_ar":"اخصبوا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They attained, obtained, had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became in the condition of having, abundance of herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the produce of the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the goods, conveniences,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comforts, of life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K.) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They became in the condition of persons whose food and milk, and the pasture of whose land, were abundant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(See the part. n.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxoSibN","text_ar":"مُخْصِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.)] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxSbt Al$~aApu","text_ar":"اخصبت الشَّاةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ewe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she-goat, obtained abundance of herbage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxSb A@ll~`hu AlmawoDiEi","text_ar":"اخصب ا@للّٰهُ المَوْضِعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God caused the place to produce herbs and pasture."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxSbt AlEiDaAhu","text_ar":"اخصبت العِضَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned as on the authority of Lth, [and in the K,] is, accord. to Az, a gross mistranscription, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxSbt","text_ar":"اخصبت"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n10758","headword_ar":"اَخْصَبُ","root":"xSb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More, and most, abundant with herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}